<TEXT>
 A man who was sustained six days by a Jarvik-7 artificial heart until undergoing a transplant has died. <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gabriel </PERSON>, 38, of <ORGANIZATION> Arnold </ORGANIZATION>, died Sunday at Presbyterian-University Hospital of <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Gabriel </PERSON> received the transplant April 7, six days after surgeons implanted the mechanical heart. He had suffered a massive heart attack March 30. <PERSON> Gabriel </PERSON> was the 18th person to receive an artificial heart at the hospital, officials said Monday. <PERSON> Gabriel </PERSON> was a production underwriter for <ORGANIZATION> Pennsylvania </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Murrysville </LOCATION> for 14 years.
