<HEAD>Arena Asks Vote Recount In Eastern El Salvador</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The rightist party that won last month's legislative elections has filed a request for a vote recount in <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, the country's easternmost province. The <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elections </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> last week announced that the rightist <ORGANIZATION> Nationalist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, or <PERSON> Arena </PERSON>, had won 30 of 60 seats in the unicameral legislature in nationwide elections held March 20. All 60 seats in the Assembly were decided, as well as municipal authorities in 262 towns and cities. The council said the incumbent <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> won 23 Assembly seats and the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conciliation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> won seven. Arena, which won 178 of the municipalities, claimed it also gained an outright majority in the Assembly. It charged the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION> with trying to `` steal'' a deputy in <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. Preliminary results from the province indicated <PERSON> Arena </PERSON> had taken two of three deputy seats. But final results released by the council gave only one to <PERSON> Arena </PERSON> and two to the <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION>. Arena filed its request for a recount on Monday. The council has until Wednesday to decided whether to grant or reject the request.
</TEXT>
