<HEAD>``The Last Emperor'' Sweeps Nine of Nine Nominations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 As expected, `` The Last Emperor'' swept the 60th Academy Awards ceremony Monday night, taking Oscars in each of its nine nominated categories including direction and Best Picture. `` I must give a Chinese kow-tow to the Academy. This is one of the strongest emotions of my life, and I ca n't hide it,'' said <PERSON> Bernardo </PERSON> <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON>, who directed the epic about <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s boy ruler <PERSON> Pu </PERSON> <PERSON> Yi </PERSON>. <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON> took the Oscar for best director, the first Italian director to win in this category. The film also won for art direction, cinematography, sound, film editing, original score, costume design, adapted screenplay and picture. It was the most Oscars won by a single movie since 1962, when `` West Side Story'' took 10 awards. The record is held by the 1959 `` Ben-Hur,'' which won 11. Producer <PERSON> Jeremy </PERSON> <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> accepted the best picture award saying, `` I must say this is certainly an imperial evening for me.'' <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON> thanked <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> for allowing him to shoot there. The director amazed the film industry by winning permission to shoot a movie with political overtones in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> and to take cameras into the fabled <LOCATION> Forbidden </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, the shrine of Chinese history. The logistics of the film's production included actors from six nations, and 19,000 extras who played the soldiers of the People's <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> It was <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON>'s second nomination for directing, the first being for `` Last Tango in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION>'' in 1973. He also received a writing nomination for his screenplay of `` The Conformist'' in 1971. `` As an Italian, a European, the Acadeny Awards always seemed like a distant ceremony: Distant, remote, something I did not belong to,'' <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON> told the Shrine Auditorium audience. `` Then one day `` The Last Emperor'' got nine nominations and everything changed immediately,'' he said. Asked backstage about the lack of acting nominations for the picture, <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON> said, `` This is a democratic election, so what can I say?''
</TEXT>
