 A fire that killed seven members of a family was blamed on a 49-year-old man whose proposal to marry the family's 22-year-old daughter was turned down, police said today. The suspect, <PERSON> Muthaswamy </PERSON> <PERSON> Krishnan </PERSON>, was turned over to police by neighbors who said he poured gasoline on the <PERSON> Sinathambi </PERSON>'s home in <LOCATION> Kotagala </LOCATION> village and set it ablaze, police Sgt. <PERSON> Nihal </PERSON> <PERSON> Muttabanda </PERSON> said by telephone from the village. He said witnesses in the tea plantation village 55 miles east of <LOCATION> Colombo </LOCATION> told him <PERSON> Krishnan </PERSON> was angry when he was rejected as a suitor by the family's daughter, <LOCATION> Padmini </LOCATION>, and learned she was to marry another man. <PERSON> Padmini </PERSON>, her father, mother and four brothers died in the blaze on Monday, <PERSON> Muttabanda </PERSON> said.
