<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Cher </PERSON> was as big a hit outside the Shrine Auditorium as inside, drawing gasps from more than a thousand fans packed into street grandstands when she stepped from her limousine in a stunning see-through gown. `` Go, go, go, go, go!'' chanted fans on each side of a red-carpeted walkway leading to the cavernous hall, as nominees arrived Monday amid a hullabaloo that has become an annual rite of the Academy Awards ceremony. <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>, who won best actress for `` Moonstruck,'' continued her tradition of outrageous outfits despite the seeming consensus among the stars this year for toned-down, mostly black fashions _ in variations of long, short, strapless, body-hugging and black-on-white or white-on-black. Arriving fashionably late in the 90-degree heat, <PERSON> Cher </PERSON> knocked the scream meter off the scale when she stepped from her limousine in a diaphanous outfit partly covered by a dark black cape and swept into the auditorium. However, for a time the Oscar ritual of hasty introductions, interviews and cheers for favorite stars gave way to a traffic jam, perhaps caused by the show's move from its longtime home at the <ORGANIZATION> Dorothy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chandler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pavilion </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> Music Center. `` Please make room for the people outside to get in!'' Oscars greeter Army Archerd pleaded over a loudspeaker as arriving members of the <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sciences </ORGANIZATION> and nominees backed up at the auditorium's doors as showtime neared. `` We are working in very tight quarters,'' said Archerd. `` The Academy has decided to be here for three years, so you better get used to it.'' `` Booooo,'' 