 for in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>' Republican presidential primary The <PERSON> Boulter </PERSON> campaign, which spent about $ 250,000, complained about <PERSON> Gilbreath </PERSON>'s deep pockets. <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, breezed to renomination in March over a little-known <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Antonio </LOCATION> professor. The incumbent has said he does not care which Republican he faces in his November bid for a fourth term. In <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Achtenberg </PERSON>, 37, campaigned Monday at transit stations and a senior citizens' home. `` We are extremely optimistic,'' she said. `` It all depends on the voter turnout. Our polls indicate it's a dead heat.'' <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> visited churches in the district on Sunday, reminding parishioners of his civil rights voting record and that of his late brother, <PERSON> Phillip </PERSON>, and late sister-in-law, <PERSON> Sala </PERSON>, who also represented the city in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Burton </PERSON>, who held the Assembly seat between 1965 and 1975, was sidelined from politics in 1983 by a cocaine addiction. The other candidates were Republicans <PERSON> Max </PERSON> <PERSON> Woods </PERSON> and <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Mavrogeorge </PERSON>, Libertarian <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Peace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Freedom </ORGANIZATION> candidate <PERSON> Melissa </PERSON> <PERSON> Ehman </PERSON>, and independents <PERSON> Hope </PERSON> <PERSON> Joles </PERSON> and <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Schmitt </PERSON>. The district is overwhelmingly Democratic, and candidates from other parties were given little chance of mounting serious opposition. If no candidate wins a majority,