accompanying the hikers. The report set off a sharp political debate along party lines, with settlers and right-wing politicians denouncing it as one-sided and hasty, and demanding the resignation of the army chief of staff. Some hikers insist Miss <PERSON> Porat </PERSON> was shot by an Arab that some saw pointing a Soviet-made rifle from a rooftop.
