<HEAD>Woman in See-Through Clothes Arrested After Near-Wrecks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PEORIA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman in a see-through, fish-net body suit disrupted traffic, caused several near-wrecks and ended up being arrested, authorities said. Police said <PERSON> Dolly </PERSON> <PERSON> May </PERSON> <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> McCloud </PERSON>, 21, of <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peoria </LOCATION>, was arrested Saturday on charges of public indecency and disorderly conduct, as well as obstructing police, authorities said. According to police, an unidentified driver reported several motorists nearly collided when they suddenly slowed to look at Ms. <PERSON> McCloud </PERSON>. Police Sgt. <PERSON> Phillip </PERSON> <PERSON> Benne </PERSON> said Ms. <PERSON> McCloud </PERSON> was wearing a see-through, fish-net body suit that exposed her chest. She was covered by other clothes from the waist down, <PERSON> Benne </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Benne </PERSON> said he saw three motorists slam on their brakes, honk their horns and wave at Ms. <PERSON> McCloud </PERSON>, who was taken to the <LOCATION> Peoria </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Jail and released after posting $ 100 cash bond. She is scheduled to appear in court on May 2.
