<HEAD>12 Arrested in Sicilian Gang Rape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAZZARINO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police arrested 12 men Tuesday and accused them of gang-raping a 21-year-old women in this Sicilian hamlet. Three other men were sought in the case. The victim was invited to a party April 4 by a group of people she considered new friends. Instead, 11 men beat and raped her in a cottage, police said. On her way back to town, she was stopped by a car with four other men. Offering her a ride, they took her back into the countryside and raped her a second time, police said. Authorities jailed seven young men Tuesday and released five others under 18 on their own recognizance.
