N>. On the issue of nuclear power, the parties put off a final decision on the fate of the unfinished nuclear plant at <LOCATION> Montalto </LOCATION> di <PERSON> Castro </PERSON> near <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION>. The Socialists had insisted the plant be converted to another form of energy production. The Christian Democrats favor completing the nuclear station.
