<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Movie director <PERSON> Bernardo </PERSON> <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON>, who was prosecuted in <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> for `` Last Tango in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION>,'' was a national hero Tuesday after `` The Last Emperor'' swept the Academy Awards. It won nine Oscars, including best picture and best director. Congratulatory messages poured in from President <PERSON> Francesco </PERSON> <PERSON> Cossiga </PERSON>, other politicians and figures in the Italian movie industry hailing the victory as a great day for <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON> said in an interview with state-run RAI-TV from <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> that he hoped the prizes would give a boost to <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s flagging movie industry Recalling his visit to the set in <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> of `` The Last Emperor,'' <PERSON> Cossiga </PERSON> said the awards `` underlined yet again the great merit of Italian cinema and its authors. `` The film was an international production but five Italians shared in the awards, for art direction, cinematography, film editing and direction <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON>, 48, won acclaim for his 1970 film `` The Conformist'' but ran into legal problems in <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> two years later because of the sexual content of `` Last Tango in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION>.'' Obscenity charges were filed against him and the stars, <PERSON> Marlon </PERSON> <PERSON> Brando </PERSON> and <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Schneider </PERSON>. They were acquitted eventually, but the movie was released for showing in <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> only last year after an appeals court ruled that what once was considered obscene need no longer be classified that way. At one point, a judge ordered all copies of the movie destroyed, but after <PERSON> Bertolucci </PERSON> appealed to then-President <PERSON> Giovanni </PERSON> <PERSON> Leone </PERSON> the court allowed copies to be kept in the National Cinem