<TEXT>
 Palestinians in this village where an <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> teen-ager was killed said Tuesday they fear retaliation by Jewish settlers once the army lifts a curfew, but they insist that Arabs are n't to blame for the girl's death. <PERSON> Beita </PERSON>'s 6,000 residents are living under a dusk-to-dawn curfew. Soldiers patrol the village, which is surrounded by thick groves of olive, fig and almond trees. Troops guard the village entrance. The army has ordered the deportation of six residents. Hundreds have been detained, and <PERSON> Beita </PERSON> residents said 60 were still being held Tuesday.
