 The chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rubber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has told shareholders a top priority this year will be eliminating about $ 3.6 billion in debt incurred in fending off Sir <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldsmith </PERSON>'s 1986 attempted takeover. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Mercer </PERSON> also said Monday he expected 1988 earnings to surpass the $ 770.5 million earned last year, which included $ 257 million from discontinued operations.
