 The stock market was mixed in light trading today as the market its digested recent gains and investors waited for fresh economic data to be released later in the week. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 2.32 at 2,098.31 by mid-afternoon. Losers slightly outnumbered gainers by about 10 to 9 in the overall tally of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 722 down, 681 up and 519 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 95.48 million shares at 2 p.m. on Wall Street. `` The volume is very light, and what it shows is that there's no enthusiasm,'' said <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Daino </PERSON>, a technical analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Smith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Barney </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Harris </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Upham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. Analysts were not surprised that the market was little changed, noting that the impressive 102.13-point rise the <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> posted last week had to be digested While the market appeared to be staying put throughout the session, most analysts agreed there are positive underpinnings for equities. `` -LRB- The market -RRB- went up a long way, and we expect it to retrench,'' said <PERSON> Hidegarde </PERSON> <PERSON> Zagorski </PERSON>, vice president of <ORGANIZATION> Prudential-Bache </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, but `` once the selling is over, it will move into higher ground.'' Meanwhile, many investors remain on the sidelines as they await the release of new economic data. While they are certain to focus on February's merchandise trade report due out on Thursday, the release of retail sales figures and a meeting of the <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Seven </ORGANIZATION> major industrial countries, both scheduled for Wednesday, are likely to attract attention. `` A lot of people are going to play it close to the vest until they see some direction from the numbers coming out,'' said <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Vandenberg </PERSON>, a vice president at <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Analysts also noted that investors are once again confronting what has become a psychological barrier at the 2,100-level on the Dow Indeed, the key market barometer touched 2,101 shortly after noon but then eased back. `` The Dow has bumped its head against that level so many times, so there is some hesitation'' when it approaches the mark, <PERSON> Zagorski </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> was the shining star in an otherwise dull auto sector, rising 3 to 146 -LCB-. Aircraft issues were lower, with <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> falling | to 46 -RCB-. The <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> said it would conduct an investigation into alleged defects in the some of the company's wide-body jets. Electronic issues were mostly higher, with <ORGANIZATION> Honeywell </ORGANIZATION> up 1 -RRB- to 70; <ORGANIZATION> Kyocera </ORGANIZATION> up 1 -RCB- to 89 -LCB-, and <PERSON> Matsushita </PERSON> up 2 -LCB- to 226. Among other actively traded <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> issues, Zayre was up 1 to 24 | and <ORGANIZATION> USX </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> was up 1 -LRB- to 33 -LRB- The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks was unchanged at 152.47. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATI