<HEAD>Western Union To Cut More Than 1,800 Workers In Restructuring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UPPER SADDLE RIVER, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> will lay off about 1,800 workers, some 25 percent of its work force, by the end of this year as part of its financial restructuring, the company said Tuesday. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Amman </PERSON>, president and chief executive officer, also said the company had established five separate business units under the restructuring. <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>'s restructuring plan, completed Dec. 30, included the $ 178 million acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> ITT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, an exchange of debt for stock and the borrowing of about $ 500 million through the sale of high-interest debentures. The plan was aimed at helping keep the communications company afloat after years of major financial losses. Western Union officials have said that without the restructuring the company would have had to file for bankruptcy protection. The layoffs will affect workers in all parts of the combined company, spokesman <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Bechtel </PERSON> said. <LOCATION> Amman </LOCATION> said in a news release that the creation of separate business units, to operate on a stand-alone basis, and the integration of <ORGANIZATION> ITT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> into <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> `` are the first steps in implementing our strategic plan to make the company more profitable.'' The business largest unit, business communications services, oversees the company's international and domestic telex and electronic mail service. Money transfer services and mailgram and telegram message services are handled by another division. The consumer communications and financial services unit will coordinate the nationwide network of 11,000 <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> agents and the company's centralized telephone bureaus A third division, priority mail services, is responsible for commercial mailgram messages, priority letters and computer letters to business and special interest groups. Western Union's advanced transmission systems supervises construction and operation of local and regional fiber optic transmission facilities for corporate customers and other communications carriers. The fifth unit is responsible for national marketing of <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>'s long distance and leased transmission servicees, along with the company's international leased line business and satellite service. <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> earned $ 88.1 million in 1987 on revenue of $ 802 million, <ORGANIZATION> Bechtel </ORGANIZATION> said.
